<br>
Ten years.<br>
Twenty-five years old now, and a far cry from the girl she once was, Kat steps off the plane and walks through a now unfamiliar airport. She takes the sunglasses off her head – there’s no need for them, it’s raining in London. <br>
“Passport, ma’am.”<br>
Dutifully she hands it over, flipping her hair over her shoulder. Airport crew got cute, she thinks. He examines her closely, and she realises this passport is from when she had brown hair and eyes – the passport she used to leave all those years ago. Quickly she yanks it away from him, giving him the newer one, depicting a white-blonde-haired, grey-eyed woman.<br>
“Thank you. Please proceed to luggage pick up.”<br>
“Thanks.”<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Proceed here, proceed there. Don’t they know how to speak normally?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> She wonders.<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Say go. Or move. Although then they’d sound like farmers.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
She shakes her head, disgusted with herself for thinking such stupid thoughts.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>It’s only so I don’t have to think about…nope. Not even gonna think it.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
“Welcome back, me.”<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CHAPTER ONE: HOMECOMING</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>welcome back to my dive<br>
welcome back to my little corner of hell<br>
welcome the way pain eats you alive</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I couldn’t return to Hogwarts – I’d finished school back home, on top of that, I was twenty-five. Couldn’t see that going over too well with teachers and students alike. <br>
“You lost, love?”<br>
I cringed at the sight before me. Some old trucker guy, standing there with a stupid grin, revealing over five missing teeth.<br>
“No, I’m fine. Thanks anyway.”<br>
I walked away as quickly as possible. <br>
Where do I start? Ten years have gone by, all too fast. I don’t know what has become of the people I once knew, because they never tried to contact me. Maybe something happened, maybe they thought I didn’t want reminders of a life that almost killed me. <br>
I suppose I knew I had to come back. Something’s up in the world I left behind, something that is threatening not just my loved ones, but Creation itself.<br>
                                                <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Allegra</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
“Da-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>ad!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->”<br>
“Al-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>lie!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->”<br>
I pouted. I hated acting liking a spoiled brat, but he just would not listen! The latest broomstick, part of the Stellar range, had come out, and I really, really, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>really</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> wanted it.<br>
“I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>need</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that broomstick if I want a chance of making the team!”<br>
“First years can’t be on the team, you know that well enough.”<br>
“Uncle Harry-&quot;<br>
“-was the exception to the rule.”<br>
“Don’t you think I’m good enough?”<br>
He hugged me and bent down to my eye level.<br>
“Of course I do. I just don’t think you need the broomstick, that’s all.”<br>
“It’s not like we can’t afford it.”<br>
Dad sighed and straightened up. “This is exactly what I wanted to avoid. You are not getting that broomstick, end of story.” He entered another shop.<br>
“It’s my birthday before I leave!” I yelled after him, lying through my teeth. No reply. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
“Malfoy Manor? Why’d yer wanna go there?”<br>
“Why?” I panicked. “Did something happen?”<br>
“No, no. I was just wonderin’.”<br>
I’d found Diagon Alley, and was busy interrogating someone from Flourish and Botts. I figured, house that big, and the Malfoys being reasonably well known, someone had to know what was going on. <br>
“Do you know how I can get there?”<br>
“Well,” said the woman, scratching her head, “yer best bet is likely Floo powder. There’s a witch down Knockturn Alley. Give ’er five Galleons and she’ll get yer where yer need to go.”<br>
“Where’s Knockturn Alley?”<br>
She grumbled something under her breath and pointed the way. “Second shop on yer left.”<br>
“<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Five</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Galleons?” I said in disbelief. I didn’t have a lot of wizard money.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Delayed reaction.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
I counted my money. Six Sickles, four Knuts…and thank God, five Galleons. I followed the directions the woman had given me, and nearly knocked over a little kid in the process.<br>
“Sorry,” I muttered sheepishly. She hadn’t even noticed and moved on.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Allegra</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I watched as the lady moved down the street. She looked kind of like Aunt Aurora.<br>
“Hey, Dad?”<br>
“Mmm…”<br>
“Where’s Aunt Aurora now?”<br>
“You know,” he said, preoccupied with a spellbook. “Jesus, these things change…”<br>
“Dad,” I admonished. I know we’re not devout Christians and everything, but still. I suppose it’s just something from my muggle side.<br>
“Sorry…you know where Aurora is.”<br>
“Yeah, but wasn’t she moving?”<br>
“Oh, yes…she’s in Australia right now.”<br>
“Australia…wow.”<br>
“Maybe one day we’ll go there,” he said absentmindedly. “What else do you need?”<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
“You seek to go somewhere. Madame Fleur knows all.”<br>
I stifled a laugh. Why else would I be in a wizard Floo travel agency called, of all things, Fly by Floo by Fleur?<br>
“Yeah. Malfoy Manor.”<br>
“It can be done. For a price.”<br>
“Right, the five Galleons. Here.”<br>
I heaped the coins on the dirty desk. She nodded gravely and took my hand. I winced as her nails dug into me.<br>
“There’s something about you, my dear. Such energy,” she murmured as she waved her free hand around my head. I pulled away.<br>
“Can I go now?”<br>
“Of course.”<br>
She led me to a fireplace and instructed me what to do. <br>
“Hasn’t changed,” I commented. “<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Malfoy Manor!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->”<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Allegra</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
“Okay, can we go now? This is boring.”<br>
Dad paid for the books and we left the shop.<br>
“Draco? Is that you?”<br>
A woman’s voice reached us, and I felt, rather than saw, Dad cringe. <br>
“Keep moving, Allegra.”<br>
Spotting what could be a funny source of embarrassment for my dad, I stopped in my tracks. “Come on, Dad. She wants to talk to you.”<br>
Well. I didn’t know it was possible for a person to look so – <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>doglike</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Honestly. She was more pug than human. If I had a camera…priceless.<br>
“Pansy…er, hello there.”<br>
“Why, Draco Malfoy, you haven’t changed one bit, handsome devil!”<br>
“Ew.”<br>
Women who fawn over my dad as though he’s some kind of superstar scare me. ‘Handsome devil’? Come on.<br>
“What <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>have</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you been doing with yourself, and who is this child?”<br>
“This-&quot; Dad seemed to swell up a bit here, “-is my daughter, Allegra.”<br>
“She’s simply gorgeous, Draco, just lovely. And is there a Mrs. Malfoy?”<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
“Okay, self. Just a note: don’t travel by Floo ever!”<br>
I stood up and dusted myself off, taking in my surroundings. <br>
“Oh, no! Miss cannot be here! Miss is-&quot;<br>
“For the love of God, shut up,” I hissed. A house elf had entered the room and was busy flipping out. “Please! Am I at the Malfoy Manor?”<br>
“Master will return soon, Master Malfoy-&quot;<br>
“Alright. Thank you and goodbye.” I placed a hand on the elf’s back, propelling her out of the room. “And not one word to Master Malfoy.”<br>
I sat down on a nearby chair. After all this time…<br>
Would he still need me as he once did? <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Allegra</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
“Perhaps we can catch up another time,” Dad said hurriedly. He tried to push me along, and Pansy – Pugface waved cheerily. I burst out laughing.<br>
“Handsome devil! Dad! Was she your girl back at Hogwarts?”<br>
He stiffened, and I knew I’d said something wrong.<br>
“Let’s go home.”<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Place hadn’t changed. Draco must have had a perfect memory, or at least one better than mine. I mean, let’s face it, kidnapping does not allow you to take in your surroundings too well, but I had the distinct feeling this room had survived the “earthquake” that had killed so many, including Draco’s parents. <br>
“What the hell?” <br>
I stared at a painting on the wall.<br>
A painting of me. Whoops. It was his mother. False alarm.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Allegra</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
“Ouch. I hate Apparating!”<br>
“Did you want to Floo it?”<br>
I grumbled. Technically, I’m not supposed to tag along when Dad Apparates. <br>
Then again, him and me aren’t fans of rules.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A bang. <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Someone’s here.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
I knew it was Draco, and the thought sent butterflies cascading into my stomach. Was I really doing the right thing? Maybe he had a whole other life now. Maybe he had a girlfriend, and kids-<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Allegra!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
What had become of Cho’s baby girl? She was an orphan, and it was supposed to our job to protect her, and I wasn’t there. <br>
“Lighten up, Dad, I was just kidding, I wasn’t gonna tell Mum nothing-&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Allegra</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I froze. Standing in our lounge was the woman from Diagon Alley. <br>
“Uh, hi.”<br>
“Allegra,” she breathed. I raised an eyebrow.<br>
“Look, lady, I’m not gonna sue you or anything for bumping into me, no scratches or anything, see?” <br>
I pulled up my pant legs so she could see. She nodded. <br>
“Allie, sweetheart? Who’s here?”<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Cho. That was the first thing I heard. Out of an eleven-year-old, I heard the voice of my long dead friend. I nearly burst into tears. <br>
Until Draco walked in.<br>
“Allie, sweetheart? Who’s here?”<br>
“Just this lady from Diagon Alley. But what are you doing here anyway?”<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kat. God. Kat.<br>
No, just Kat,</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I laughed uncomfortably. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Just…me.<br>
You can’t be here.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
“Excuse me? Why are you here?”<br>
“Allegra. Upstairs.”<br>
“Dad-&quot;<br>
“Now!”<br>
“But-&quot;<br>
“Allegra, you are going to march up those stairs and not move from your room until I tell you. Go!”<br>
I watched in surprise as she did just that. Anyone talked to me like that would’ve been six feet under in a matter of seconds.<br>
“Quite the little soldier.”<br>
“Don’t. You can’t do that, come in here and make random judgements on everyone.”<br>
“Draco, I…”<br>
“Stop! I don’t want to hear it!”<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>You can’t stop me from talking. I had to come back, Draco. Something’s going on. Something bad, you must be able to feel it. If I know all the way back in New Zealand, you do too.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
He shook his head. “Nothing bad is coming. Tell me why you’re really here.”<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Because something is about to happen! </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
“I’m…I’m married. It’s too late for us.”<br>
I stepped forward and held his face in my hands. I had to reach up a way, and pull him down to my level. “Never too late for anything. You know that at least.”<br>
“What the hell is going on?”<br>
I turned. “<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hermione?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->”<br>
She stood there, with an indignant look on her face. That image of strength was ruined by her lower lip trembling, as though she was about to cry. It took me three seconds to register what was going on.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>You married my best friend?<br>
You don’t know the full story.<br>
What, there’s more? Let me guess-you both tripped down the aisle and said ‘hey, look, a priest. I do’?<br>
You left! You left me, and we had a destiny that I covered on my own! Our fate became mine!<br>
Not yours alone! You had Hermione!<br>
But she’s not you.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Stunned, I ran out of words. Hermione barged between us.<br>
“Who the hell are you?”<br>
“Mione, it’s me, it’s Kat-&quot;<br>
“Kat?” She searched my eyes. I shrugged.<br>
“Hey. How’re you been the past ten years?”<br>
“What are you doing here?”<br>
“I don’t want to repeat myself. Can we sit?”<br>
Hermione took a seat next to Draco, possessively draping an arm around his waist. I couldn’t help it, but the first thing that came to mind was ‘is she SuperSlut now or something?’. I know it’s terrible.<br>
“Why are you here?” Hermione repeated. <br>
“The answer, my friends, is blowin’ in the wind. I think there’s something of the Big Bad variety headed your way.”<br>
“You came back for that? Didn’t think we could handle it?”<br>
“Hermione. Please. I know what you’re capable of, and it’s enough to send some running. But I thought you may need my help.”<br>
“Help? How could you help?” she snorted.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>If you love this woman you will get her away from me. <br>
Is that a threat?<br>
It’s a bloody promise. That’s not the Hermione I knew.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Allegra</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I crouched at the bottom of the stairs, listening carefully. Apparently, Dad knew the woman I’d smacked into in the alley. Mum did too-although she wasn’t all that happy about it. <br>
“Help? How could you help?”<br>
Silence fell, but the tension floated all the way up the stairs.<br>
“Hermione, let her talk.”<br>
“I’m sorry, but she comes back here, expecting everything to be the same? It’s not right.”<br>
I heard Mum’s footsteps get closer to me, and I took flight to my room.<br>
