The unmistakeable sound of laughter reached me.<br>
“Come out!” I shouted. Then it struck me. I’d fallen through the floor, shouldn’t the big gaping hole still be there?<br>
A fast glance upwards answered that question. Sealed over. No light. In fact I could barely see two feet in front me.<br>
I felt someone rush past me and the fear started coursing through me again.<br>
“Stop!”<br>
They paid no attention.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
