“Out!”<br>
“I’m going, I’m going…”<br>
I opened the door for him.<br>
He walked straight into Draco.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Allegra</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I sat impatiently waiting for everyone to get up. Finally, Mum got up and went over to the tree. She threw me a soft package.<br>
“Open that while you wait.”<br>
I tore into it. A neatly folded robe the colour of an apple sat there. I looked at Mum.<br>
“It’s for Beauxbatons,” she explained. “They haven’t got house colours there.”<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Beauxbatons.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
“Mum, I don’t know if I can go.”<br>
“Of course you can.”<br>
“No, really. What if…what if something happens? What if I do something?”<br>
“Allie. You’ll be fine.”<br>
“You don’t know that.”<br>
