“You won’t have to.”<br>
“But if Draco ever found out…”<br>
“He’d understand.”<br>
“It’s Draco, Harry. When has he ever understood me?”<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kat</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
“Always.”<br>
I nodded. So many things had changed, yet that one fact remained the same. <br>
Just as another did – I didn’t belong here. It was all what could have been, not what was.<br>
“So. Bye.”<br>
“Wait. You’re still going?!”<br>
“Don’t <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>do</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> this. Enough already!”<br>
“Can’t you see I just want you to stay?”<br>
